title: GM's driverless car company Cruise is under investigation by several agencies
description: Cruise hired a law firm to investigate the start-up's interactions with regulators after a Cruise vehicle dragged a pedestrian on October 2. Multiple government agencies are now examining the crash.

title: Justin Timberlake teases first new album in 5 years with single 'Selfish'
description: The Grammy Award-winner's track comes in run up to the March 15 release of his new album, Everything I Thought It Was.

title: Sweary parrots become unlikely stars at a British zoo ($#@%!)
description: The profane parrots please patrons, despite the staff's fears that visitors might be scandalized from hearing so much salty language from the birds.

title: JN.1 takes over as the most prevalent COVID-19 variant. Here's what you need to know
description: The CDC estimates that up to 86% of new COVID-19 cases stem from the latest mutation. The virus continues to evolve so rapidly that "our immune systems have not been able to keep up," an expert says.

title: Trump testifies in the E. Jean Carroll trial
description: In all, Trump spoke for less than a minute. He insisted that his previous recorded statement about the allegations was true and that he did not intend to harm her.

title: Many experts feared a recession. Instead, the economy has continued to soar
description: The U.S. economy grew substantially faster in the final months of 2023 than forecasters had expected. For all of last year, the economy grew 3.1% — defying forecasts of a likely recession.

title: Bipartisan boarder deal at risk of collapse under pressure from Trump
description: A bipartisan border deal is at risk after Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell suggested the politics around the agreement have shifted.

title: Senate border negotiations forge ahead despite pressure from Trump
description: Senate negotiators are continuing to work on a bipartisan border deal even after Minority Leader Mitch McConnell suggested the politics around the agreement have shifted.

title: Ex-Trump adviser Peter Navarro sentenced to 4 months for contempt of Congress
description: Former Trump White House trade adviser Peter Navarro was convicted last year for defying a subpoena from the House committee investigating the Jan. 6 Capitol attack.

title: Criminal trial for Spain's former soccer head is proposed for his unwanted kiss
description: A high court judge also says three men who pressured Jenni Hermoso to absolve Luis Rubiales — by acting together in an attempt "to break the will" of the star forward — could also face charges.

title: A U.S. scientist's tea recipe has Brits aghast. Salt? Warm milk? The horror!
description: Some 250 years after Americans ruined a lot of British tea in Boston Harbor, a U.S. chemist's salty tip for the perfect cup has prompted an intervention from the U.S. Embassy in London.

title: Up First briefing: Boeing faces production caps, Haley bets on South Carolina
description: The FAA laid out a plan for Boeing 737 Max 9 jets to resume flying, but also hit the company with production caps. Former South Carolina Gov. Nikki Haley pins her presidential hopes on her home state.

title: Housing is now unaffordable for a record half of all U.S. renters, study finds
description: A new Harvard analysis finds people across income levels got squeezed by rent hikes during the pandemic. The market has lost millions of low-rent places, and new construction is mostly high-end.

title: Young voters focus more on issues than candidates in 2024 presidential election
description: Voters under 30 tend to lean left of center overall and could make a major difference for Democratic candidates. Will they turn out in strong enough numbers to help President Biden win reelection?

title: Regulators target fees for consumers who are denied a purchase for insufficient funds
description: It's the latest salvo in the government's campaign against so-called "junk fees," which President Biden said last year harm "working folks" and drive up costs for consumers.

title: The colonoscopies were free but the 'surgical trays' came with $600 price tags
description: Health providers may bill however they choose, including in ways that could leave patients with unexpected bills for "free" care. Preventive care left an Illinois couple with "surgical tray" charges.

title: His spacecraft sprung a leak. Then this NASA astronaut accidentally broke a record
description: NASA astronaut Frank Rubio holds the record for the longest U.S. space flight, but he wasn't trying to earn that title.

title: Japan's village with the oldest population is wooing young residents to survive
description: Some Japanese are trying to reinvigorate their country's most aged village — where two-thirds of residents are over 65.

title: Delegate tracker: Trump leads GOP presidential candidates on road to nomination
description: How many delegates does each candidate have in the 2024 Republican presidential nomination race? NPR keeps track.

title: So long, presidential debates? Why we may not see Trump, Biden or Haley face off
description: The political debate seems to have become an endangered species, and there are no assurances we'll see Trump, Biden or Haley share the stage this year.

title: Texas cold leaves alligators frozen underwater, but still alive. Here's how
description: Alligators rely on external sources to regulate their body temperatures — so during winter, they will go into brumation. A viral video captured the phenomenon during the Texas winter freeze.

title: Why don't GOP voters care about electability this year?
description: Nikki Haley's pitch is that she can beat Joe Biden. But now that she's lost — twice — voters are signaling they aren't concerned about electability as much as a candidate that shares their values.

title: Man is sentenced to death for arson attack at Japanese anime studio that killed 36
description: A Japanese court sentenced a man to death after finding him guilty of murder for carrying out a shocking arson attack on an anime studio in Kyoto, Japan, that killed 36 people.

title: Italy's lower chamber of parliament approves deal with Albania to house migrants
description: The proposal, which passed 155-115 with two abstentions in the Chamber of Deputies, now goes to the Senate, where Premier Giorgia Meloni's right-wing forces also have a comfortable majority.

title: The FAA lays out a path for Boeing 737 Max 9 to fly again, but new concerns surface
description: While the Federal Aviation Administration says the grounded 737 Max 9 aircraft can resume flying after inspections, the agency imposed sweeping jet production restrictions at Boeing factories.
